Answer 6:-
HTML5 introduced several significant advancements over its previous versions, offering numerous advantages. Firstly, it provided better support for multimedia elements like video and audio, eliminating the need for third-party plugins. Additionally, HTML5 introduced a more semantic markup structure, enabling developers to define the meaning of content using new elements such as `<header>`, `<footer>`, and `<nav>`. The improved form controls and input types offered better user experience and validation options. HTML5 also brought support for offline storage and caching through features like Local Storage and Application Cache. Furthermore, it enhanced the ability to create dynamic web applications with the introduction of the Canvas element and the WebSocket API. Overall, HTML5 brought modernization and enriched capabilities to web development.
